    "Of these, 807 studies advanced to the full-text review, and 245 studies were ultimately included in this scoping review (Methods, Fig. 1).",
    "The characteristics of these studies are provided in Supplementary Appendix 5.",
    "The studies spanned various application areas of integrated models for diverse infectious diseases.",
    "Overall, 26 infectious diseases were investigated using integrated models (Supplementary Appendix 6).",
    "The majority of these studies focused on COVID-19 (148 studies, 60%), followed by influenza (18 studies, 7%), dengue (4 studies, 2%), and HIV (3 studies, 1%)."
